 Office is required to secure copyright  Copyright Endurance Generally  copyright extends from the moment of a work s creation to 70 years after the author s death  See the document  Copyright Basics pp  5 6  below  for a more extensive treatment  Links to Copyright Information The Library of Congress maintains an extensive repository of copyright information  Some of the more informative documents for educators are the following  Copyright Basics requires Adobe Acrobat Reader  Reproduction of Copyrighted Works by Educators and Librarians  requires Adobe Acrobat Reader  Copyright FAQ  Frequently Asked Questions  Title 17 of US Code  Copyright statutes  The Digital Millenium Copyright Act  long 50 pp  PDF  The DMCA Summary Copyright Registration Information Copyright Registration for Sound Recordings Copyright Infringement Allegations and Agents The Interlibrary Loan office in Preston Library maintains copies of these works Information Technology Information Security Cadets Faculty and Staff Computer Labs Network Information Print  Copy  and Fax Services Policies IT Staff Technology Steering Committee Help Desk Monday   Friday  7 00 am   4 00 pm  Self Service Portal P   540  464 7643 F   540  464 7222 Help vmi edu Email IT Webmaster Information Technology 315 Nichols Engineering Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450  Information Technology Information Security Cadets Faculty and Staff Computer Labs Network Information Print  Copy  and Fax Services Policies IT Staff Technology Steering Committee Help Desk Monday   Friday  7 00 am   4 00 pm  Self Service Portal P   540  464 7643 F   540  464 7222 Help vmi edu Email IT Webmaster Information Technology 315 Nichols Engineering Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA 24450 Information Technology Information Security Cadets Faculty and Staff Computer Labs Network Information Print  Copy  and Fax Services Policies IT Staff Technology Steering Committee Information Technology Information Technology Information Sec